            <h3>Streaming Media Technologies</h3>

            <p><a href="/">Dr. Lavian is intimately familiar</a> with the Internet protocol suite (TCP/IP) and is proficient in networking and communications technologies, including:</p>

            <ul>
              <li>Multimedia, audio, and video streaming.</li>
              <li>Video/audio conferencing, streaming media, and music streaming over TCP/IP protocol stack using standard Internet protocols such as TCP, UDP, IP, HTTP, HTML, and Web services.</li>
              <li>Integration of streaming media with SIP, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/internet-expert-witness/">Internet protocols</a> (TCP/IP), and streaming systems as the backbone of unified communicants.</li>
              <li>Integration of such protocols and services with short message technologies, including text messaging, SMS, MMS, <a href="/communications-expert-witness/messaging-and-chat-expert-witness/">Instant Messaging (IM), and chat applications</a>. Streaming media shares underlying <a href="/communications-expert-witness/voice-over-ip-voip-expert/">VoIP</a> protocols such as SIP and RTP.</li>
